headline: Target earnings, Fed commentary, housing data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton previews the biggest stories to come throughout the next trading week, including earnings out from major retailers such as Target (TGT), Home Depot (HD), and Lowe's (LOW), as well as commentary out from quite a number of Federal Reserve officials, and US housing data. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Is Intuit (INTU) a Buy as Wall Street Analysts Look Optimistic?
summary: The average brokerage recommendation (ABR) for Intuit (INTU) is equivalent to a Buy. The overly optimistic recommendations of Wall Street analysts make the effectiveness of this highly sought-after metric questionable. So, is it worth buying the stock?
